President Donald Trump took questions in the Oval Office on Thursday, shortly after signing several more executive orders on his fourth day in office. Asked for reaction on a U.S. judge temporarily blocking his executive order ending birthright citizenship, Trump said, “Obviously, we’ll appeal it. They put it before a certain judge in Seattle, I guess. Right? And there’s no surprises with that judge.”
